<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,324,267,293]" box="[189,324,267,293]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,267,293]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1398,313,375]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The species is named in honour of Dr. Petra De Block, who collected it at the Baies de Sakalaves and who played an important role in making the inventory of Madagascan 
<taxonomicName box="[1016,1142,348,374]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="family">Rubiaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
